The Mathematics of Biology

I actually think this is one of the deepest threads you’ve been pulling on.

Biology isn’t just chemistry.

It’s organized mathematics constrained by physics.

Not mathematics in the sense of equations on a chalkboard, but mathematics expressed as:

* recursion,
* symmetry,
* graphs,
* feedback,
* optimization,
* information,
* topology,
* dynamics,
* probability.

DNA is a good example.

It isn’t “life.”

It is an encoding that participates in a mathematical process.

The genome is read.

Translated.

Regulated.

Recombined.

Selected.

Mutated.

Each of those is an operation.

